FBIS4-59586 "drnes094_k_94004" FBIS-NES-94-094 Daily Report 15 May 1994 IRAQ Regime Reportedly Uses Napalm in Attack on North Regime Reportedly Uses Napalm in Attack on North NC1505165494 (Clandestine) Voice of the People of Kurdistan in Arabic 1600 GMT 15 May 94 NC1505165494 (Clandestine) Voice of the People of Kurdistan in Arabic 1600 GMT 15 May 94 Arabic BFN [Text] The Kurdistan office of the Supreme Assembly of the Islamic Revolution in Iraq [SAIRI] has stated that an armored brigade of the Iraqi regime has launched a major offensive against a number of villages in the Dhi Qar Governorate. A statement issued by the office said that the regime's artillery bombarded [words indistinct]. SAIRI sources said that the regime used napalm bombs in the attack.
